{"TopicId":205937,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Fun Fact Thread! (previously fun fact for the day, not limited to 1 per day anymore.)","CreatedByName":"Hyperspace Industries","CreatedById":212417,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-11T07:42:52Z","PageNum":42,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T05:24:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273403\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681618992\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s horrible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022450\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://web-tulun.ru/info/images/photoalbum/album_21/vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u0022900\u0022 src=\u0022https://primpack.ru/media/k2/items/cache/d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA space food.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSaint","CreatedById":70033,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T06:14:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273415\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681622648\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://web-tulun.ru/info/images/photoalbum/album_21/vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022450\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://web-tulun.ru/info/images/photoalbum/album_21/vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://primpack.ru/media/k2/items/cache/d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u0022900\u0022 src=\u0022https://primpack.ru/media/k2/items/cache/d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA space food.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022I-dont-want-to-live-on-this-planet-anymo\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.11\u0022 height=\u0022202\u0022 width=\u0022360\u0022 src=\u0022https://external-content.duckduckgo.com/iu/?u=http://abovethelaw.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/I-dont-want-to-live-on-this-planet-anymore-meme.jpg\u0026amp;f=1\u0026amp;nofb=1\u0026amp;ipt=8210081ff1ac520f9abe3fea28e80a474e79d59a2d591622d13c3cf4076eecda\u0026amp;ipo=images\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve9728","CreatedById":206195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T06:22:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273403\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681618992\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s horrible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are three acceptable ways to drink beer: bottle, draft, and straight out of the cask.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got a ex from there before. I asked her and her answer is she also don\u0027t know why. Perhaps the people who first started doing this thought it would be more convenient - after all, you don\u0027t have to wash the cups. And the most important thing is, it\u0027s fresh: you need to drink it ASAP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe way they drink is buy the beer from the street. Carry it home in bag and hang it on the corner of the table. Poke a small hole on the bag and squeeze the glass\u00A0against the bag to pour the beer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T07:08:56Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 07:08  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by steve9728\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T09:16:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273403\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681618992\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are three acceptable ways to drink beer: bottle, draft, and straight out of the cask.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2b Wheeled draft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221181376_original.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002283.25\u0022 height=\u0022800\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://ic.pics.livejournal.com/mib55/39777448/1181376/1181376_original.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pivo-05.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002268.85\u0022 height=\u0022705\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://retailer.ru/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pivo-05.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002275badae97fdbf62eccaa48642f8ea92d.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002263.50\u0022 height=\u0022508\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://vyatkawalks.ru/upload/medialibrary/75b/75badae97fdbf62eccaa48642f8ea92d.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pivo-01.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002291.33\u0022 height=\u0022548\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://retailer.ru/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pivo-01.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTraditionally, via the 3-liter glass jar, but just because there was no enough strong plastic bags.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe same about kvass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022188639_12_trinixy_ru.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002252.19\u0022 height=\u0022334\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.trinixy.ru/pics6/20200213/188639_12_trinixy_ru.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022865923-1562719256.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.67\u0022 height=\u0022512\u0022 width=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.nastroy.net/pic/images/201907/865923-1562719256.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt may look undermanding, but it is still a standard 750-liter pressure vessel with torispherical heads.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting fact: its nominal volume is 900 l, but every time I had seen it, it was written 750 l.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EWho knows, why...\u003C/s\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt was based on the 500 kg capable trailer chassis. So, probably a compromise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pricep-TAPZ-755.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.00\u0022 height=\u0022330\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://sptechnika.ru/wp-content/uploads/pricep-TAPZ-755.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso it\u0027s equipped with a 30 l water barrel to wash the cups!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe hatch is 500 mm in diameter, so you can get through even in an escape spacesuit (550 mm is required).\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso, the barrel is two-hulled. A steel outer hull and an aluminium inner one.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMaybe, good for a Kerbal lunar habitat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpd.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.trucksinscale.com/viewtopic.php?id=317\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.trucksinscale.com/viewtopic.php?id=317\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00220_171d8c_f545af8d_XL.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.25\u0022 height=\u0022722\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://img-fotki.yandex.ru/get/223280/33717193.e/0_171d8c_f545af8d_XL.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T12:23:09Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 12:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T12:52:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273390\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681615203\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206195\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve9728\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, steve9728 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Qingdao, people use plastic bag to hold the fresh beer\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d674d794d444f77457a6333566d54/img/c8d2d2859f22455f9df266b8aa05d071/c8d2d2859f22455f9df266b8aa05d071.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Draft beer served in plastic bags in Qingdao - CGTN\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.26\u0022 width=\u0022935\u0022 src=\u0022https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d674d794d444f77457a6333566d54/img/c8d2d2859f22455f9df266b8aa05d071/c8d2d2859f22455f9df266b8aa05d071.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://shanghaimetalcorporation.wordpress.com/2014/09/09/only-in-china-drink-beer-straight-from-a-plastic-bag/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://shanghaimetalcorporation.wordpress.com/2014/09/09/only-in-china-drink-beer-straight-from-a-plastic-bag/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273403\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681618992\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s horrible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are three acceptable ways to drink beer: bottle, draft, and straight out of the cask.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelllllllllll... There \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eare\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E exceptions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn HS some friends and I drove past a rival HS party that was being broken up by the cops.\u00A0 Half hour later, everyone is gone and the street is quiet.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone hopped the fence and stole the keg.\u00A0 Still had beer in it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat someone didn\u0027t steal the cups.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, Jenius us, we made do.\u00A0 Drank beer out of empty Doritos bags!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T14:06:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWay #4.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.npr.org/2008/07/28/93001529/beer-drinking-tree-shrews-sober-as-judges\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.npr.org/2008/07/28/93001529/beer-drinking-tree-shrews-sober-as-judges\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve9728","CreatedById":206195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T14:30:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273532\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681653961\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWay #4.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.npr.org/2008/07/28/93001529/beer-drinking-tree-shrews-sober-as-judges\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.npr.org/2008/07/28/93001529/beer-drinking-tree-shrews-sober-as-judges\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me one day I saw a squirrel probably ate some \u0022expired\u0022 berries.\u00A0The pace and demeanour are highly similar to a friend of mine who loves to drink.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T15:11:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273539\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681655433\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206195\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve9728\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, steve9728 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me one day I saw a squirrel probably ate some \u0022expired\u0022 berries.\u00A0The pace and demeanour are highly similar to a friend of mine who loves to drink.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey - speaking of spirits (or at least it\u0027s cousin)... what is the \u0027scene\u0027 in China these days with regard to whiskey?\u00A0 I know that Japan has a history of brewing Sake which led into an interest in whiskey, but I\u0027m unfamiliar with Chinese distillates.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes China have a similar \u0027home brew\u0027 hard alcohol?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo folks there have a taste for Scotch, or Bourbon or Irish whiskeys?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(oh - and not just as something you mix with Coke - but as something enjoyed for itself, neat or on the rocks; people who mix drinks are worth pitying.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T15:13:20Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 03:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve9728","CreatedById":206195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T15:59:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681657902\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey - speaking of spirits (or at least it\u0027s cousin)... what is the \u0027scene\u0027 in China these days with regard to whiskey?\u00A0 I know that Japan has a history of brewing Sake which led into an interest in whiskey, but I\u0027m unfamiliar with Chinese distillates.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes China have a similar \u0027home brew\u0027 hard alcohol?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo folks there have a taste for Scotch, or Bourbon or Irish whiskeys?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(oh - and not just as something you mix with Coke - but as something enjoyed for itself, neat or on the rocks; people who mix drinks are worth pitying.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf only some kind \u0022home brew\u0022, the answer is yes.\u00A0Broadly, there\u0027s Baijiu (\u767D\u9152 White wine), Huangjiu (\u9EC4\u9152, Yellow wine). Baijiu is distilled wine and Huangjiu\u00A0fermented wine.\u00A0Basically, all starchy crops have been made into wine by us Chinese, including but not limited to rice, wheat, sorghum, barley, and sweet potatoes.\u00A0One of the homemade wine made by rice called \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jiuniang\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESweet Ferment Rice\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(\u91AA\u7CDF) is particularly tasty, looks harmless and you will have no problems with it for the first 5 minutes - I can\u0027t guarantee what happens after that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022u=3969834351,802085483\u0026amp;fm=253\u0026amp;fmt=auto\u0026amp;a\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.76\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 width=\u0022749\u0022 src=\u0022https://img1.baidu.com/it/u=3969834351,802085483\u0026amp;fm=253\u0026amp;fmt=auto\u0026amp;app=138\u0026amp;f=JPEG?w=749\u0026amp;h=500\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow bad it can b........\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Shaoxing, that\u0027s a kind of wine made by rice called \u0022\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huangjiu#Types\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDaughter Red\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(\u5973\u513F\u7EA2)\u0022. It means that after the birth of a daughter in the family, after the kid\u0027s first month, the father will choose a few jars of wine and bury them in the ground (today it\u0027s sealed and kept in somewhere of the house). When the daughter was married, he would take them out and serve them to his guests. Some of them made by sweet potato. You can think it\u0027s some kind vodka. Video about how people make this little monster:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1tG411N7cg/?spm_id_from=333.337.search-card.all.click\u0026amp;vd_source=6fef304b8d0c4737896e6b702ddfbfb3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1tG411N7cg/?spm_id_from=333.337.search-card.all.click\u0026amp;vd_source=6fef304b8d0c4737896e6b702ddfbfb3\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut meanwhile, there\u0027s something call \u0022medicinal wine (\u836F\u9152)\u0022. Just like my UK classmates said to me that \u0022better don\u0027t ask what\u0027s in the pie\u0022, kindly suggest don\u0027t ask what they put in the wine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasically, this thing is herbs soaked in Baijiu and Huangjiu. But in addition to the regular medicinal plants, the things steeped in it include but are not limited to wasps, centipedes, snakes, turtles, and stags\u0027 reproductive organs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XttP-fznefkf9785821.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.00\u0022 height=\u0022396\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022http://n.sinaimg.cn/translate/196/w600h396/20180421/XttP-fznefkf9785821.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022If you let me know what\u0027s in, no thanks, I don\u0027t dare to drink it\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe whisky or other wine from outside of China, yes, we like to drink it. Fun fact is, in the club they not only mix with coke, but also mixed in the tea drink which added sugar.\u00A0On my return from the UK, I brought back bottles of Glenlivet for my parents and my gf\u0027s parents respectively from Heathrow. Judging by their facial expressions and subsequent developments, it was a great gift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T17:00:28Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 05:00  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by steve9728\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T17:27:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681660751\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206195\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve9728\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, steve9728 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022If you let me know what\u0027s in, no thanks, I don\u0027t dare to drink it\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUrk.\u00A0 No kidding!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Although... I have \u0027drank the worm\u0027!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve9728","CreatedById":206195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T17:35:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681666039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUrk.\u00A0 No kidding!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Although... I have \u0027drank the worm\u0027!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood news is that unlike the tequila, you don\u0027t need to eat the \u0027contents\u0027, you just need to drink the liquid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T17:52:09Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 05:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by steve9728\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T17:40:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681660751\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206195\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve9728\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, steve9728 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsubsequent developments\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh-ho! Sounds like something good happened\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;p\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/971609041_P.png\u0022 title=\u0022;p\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve9728","CreatedById":206195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T18:02:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, as long-winded as this may seem, but it\u0027s still important to mention that please drink responsibly, don\u0027t let the minors drink and don\u0027t drive after drunk.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T18:03:25Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 06:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by steve9728\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T18:15:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273347\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681603227\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is easily parried by many planned economies retaining corporate structures for ease of management.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is that word where the state and private corporations work hand in hand in a centrally planned way? \u00A0 There is a word for that, dang it. \u00A0If only Mussolini were here to jog my memory, lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T20:15:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681668908\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is that word where the state and private corporations work hand in hand in a centrally planned way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0410\u0434\u043C\u0438\u043D\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043D\u043E-\u043A\u043E\u043C\u0430\u043D\u0434\u043D\u044B\u0439 \u0433\u043E\u0441\u043A\u0430\u043F\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043B\u0438\u0437\u043C\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdministrative-command state capitalism.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681668908\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a word for that, dang it. \u00A0If only Mussolini were here to jog my memory, lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a word with another meaning. This word means \u0022state is everything, person is nothing; state is for everything the person is and does, person does everything via and for the state\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022Order\u0022 pole of evil, opposite to the \u0022Chaos\u0022 pole known as anarchy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut this happily works with free trade, it\u0027s perpendicular to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T20:18:25Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 08:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T20:28:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273415\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681622648\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://web-tulun.ru/info/images/photoalbum/album_21/vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022450\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://web-tulun.ru/info/images/photoalbum/album_21/vodka2_t2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://primpack.ru/media/k2/items/cache/d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u0022900\u0022 src=\u0022https://primpack.ru/media/k2/items/cache/d81dde7813bd99a2f6a5498a2ec932ec_XL.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA space food.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat makes more sense,\u00A0spirits don\u0027t contain co2 and are stable.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nHere in Norway you buy whine on bags but they come inside an cardboard box. This has the benefit for wine that unlike bottles no air is added then you empty it so it last longer mostly empty.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou can not buy champagne on\u00A0\u00A0bags for good reasons.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nChampagne and other\u00A0sparkling wine\u00A0bottles is not aged in\u00A0 open racks as standard but in arrays of boxes so one bottle exploding will not create an chain reaction \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681668908\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is that word where the state and private corporations work hand in hand in a centrally planned way? \u00A0 There is a word for that, dang it. \u00A0If only Mussolini were here to jog my memory, lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUS during WW 2. Lots of the economy was centrally\u00A0 planned for the war effort, as in most of manufacturing. It did not affect businesses who was not relevant for the war economy at not directly.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nAn car dealership would have problem getting new cars to sell as the car factories was producing for the war as an example.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt worked pretty well, all knew it was for the duration of the war only and most supported the war.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI say most active countries during WW 2 did something like this but the US is most famous.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T21:05:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681668908\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is that word where the state and private corporations work hand in hand in a centrally planned way? \u00A0 There is a word for that, dang it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe French would call it \u003Cem\u003Edirigisme\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a lot softer than German Gleichschaltung and privatization. Mussolini relied heavily on the trade unions (fascio) as the sources of \u0027social\u0027 control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[snip]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-16T21:49:14Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2023 09:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vanamonde\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-16T21:49:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy does politics keep getting dragged into the Fun Facts thread? As always, please avoid that.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-17T05:01:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224273403\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681618992\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/15/2023 at 9:23 PM, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s horrible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are three acceptable ways to drink beer: bottle, draft, and straight out of the cask.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou neglected, \u0022Off a fellow mammal that\u0027s recently dismounted from a brass pole.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-17T12:43:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://ufosightingshotspot.blogspot.com/2022/03/giant-ufo-at-bottom-of-ocean-off-coast.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://ufosightingshotspot.blogspot.com/2022/03/giant-ufo-at-bottom-of-ocean-off-coast.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/MHBfhv42afI?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Giant UFO at the bottom of the ocean off coast Peru\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe bathtub stopper? Then why two?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve9728","CreatedById":206195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-18T08:26:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEvery spring (it\u0027s about that time now) when the rivers been frozen in northern China is about to melt, in order to prevent ice flooding, that needs the gov to blasting the ice. Some easy to reach and not that dangerous places, such as the Heilongjiang River on the Russian- Chinese border, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1L64y1S7G7/?spm_id_from=333.337.search-card.all.click\u0026amp;vd_source=6fef304b8d0c4737896e6b702ddfbfb3\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ecan be blasted by going directly onto the ice and installing explosives.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224ee160ec-76f9-4fcf-8f12-3ad5ccbc17b0_zsi\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.14\u0022 height=\u0022393\u0022 width=\u0022700\u0022 src=\u0022https://i2.chinanews.com.cn/simg/ypt/2023/230406/4ee160ec-76f9-4fcf-8f12-3ad5ccbc17b0_zsite.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut some river, such as Yellow River, that needs army \u003Cspan\u003Eusing the artillery\u003C/span\u003E or even air force to send the bombers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002264.83\u0022 height=\u0022389\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/X7zVn6c/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-18T08:30:09Z\u0022 title=\u002204/18/2023 08:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 18, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by steve9728\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-18T19:04:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost military buffs know that the Israelis made a Kalashnikov rifle derivative (twice removed, having studied the Finnish Valmet) called the Galil.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00228033507906_2847b1b4f4_b.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002258.50\u0022 height=\u0022585\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022 src=\u0022https://live.staticflickr.com/8177/8033507906_2847b1b4f4_b.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, not everyone knows that the eponymous Yisrael Galil was born Yisrael Balashnikov, and only decided to change his surname midway through the rifle\u0027s development. His employers were reportedly relieved, having been rather cross to release a Kalashnikov-derived Balashnikov rifle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"farmerben","CreatedById":190194,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-18T21:38:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/NT8-b5YEyjo?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022The Soviet Union\u0027s Deadly Abandoned Nuclear Generators\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Soviets built 2500 terrestrial RTGs.\u00A0 For lighthouses and radio transmitters in remote territory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-18T21:52:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224274260\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681844642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost military buffs know that the Israelis made a Kalashnikov rifle derivative (twice removed, having studied the Finnish Valmet) called the Galil.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://live.staticflickr.com/8177/8033507906_2847b1b4f4_b.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00228033507906_2847b1b4f4_b.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002258.50\u0022 height=\u0022585\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022 src=\u0022https://live.staticflickr.com/8177/8033507906_2847b1b4f4_b.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, not everyone knows that the eponymous Yisrael Galil was born Yisrael Balashnikov, and only decided to change his surname midway through the rifle\u0027s development. His employers were reportedly relieved, having been rather cross to release a Kalashnikov-derived Balashnikov rifle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes that would sound stupid , now they could just give it an number like G-36 or M-16.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn Norwegian army an M-72 was an lightweight single use RPG, M-71 was an standard army field jacket. Do not confuse the two.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNow the M-72 has an 72 mm diameter, one alcoholic found he could fit an bottle inside his M-72. Good plan except someone else picked his up during an alarm at an exercise and then informed sergeant that he had an live M-72, all the training ones was empty. Retrieving an bottle of alcohol but not able to pin it back to the guy \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-18T21:55:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224274308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681854752\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Norwegian army an M-72 was an lightweight single use RPG, M-71 was an standard army field jacket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe US in WWII had a lot of various very different M1s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224274308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681854752\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow the M-72 has an 72 mm diameter, one alcoholic found he could fit an bottle inside his M-72.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDuring WWII, Soviet lend-lease stevedores spread the myth that every Sherman came with a bottle of whiskey stuffed down its (plugged-up) barrel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}